Four men have been arrested after cocaine, ecstasy and heroin worth Â£286,000 were discovered in Glasgow. Four men arrested over Glasgow cocaine and heroin haul Four men have been arrested after cocaine, ecstasy and heroin worth &pound;286,000 were discovered in Glasgow.
Police said the drugs were seized during raids across the Castlemilk area of the city at 08:00 on Thursday. 
Officers searched commercial units in the Glenwood Industrial Estate and three homes in Dougrie Place, Cressland Drive and Drakemire Avenue. 
Two men aged 20, and two others aged 25 and 53, are due to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Friday.
 